abstract: Seven Democratic presidential candidates will stand on stage this week in Los Angeles, a pool of survivors who have withstood almost a year on the campaign trail, sustained attacks from rivals in both major political parties and five rounds of high-pressure debates.

lead_paragraph: CLINTON, Iowa — Seven Democratic presidential candidates will stand on stage this week in Los Angeles, a pool of survivors who have withstood almost a year on the campaign trail, sustained attacks from rivals in both major political parties and five rounds of high-pressure debates.
headline_main: Turbulence Shakes Democrats Going Into Final Debate of 2019
headline_print_headline: Turbulence Shakes Democrats Going Into Final Debate of 2019

abstract: Five aides to a House Democrat who plans to become a Republican are resigning, saying his party switch “does not align with the values we brought to this job when we joined his office."

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Five aides to a House Democrat who plans to become a Republican are resigning, saying his party switch “does not align with the values we brought to this job when we joined his office."
headline_main: Five Aides to Party-Switching House Lawmaker Resign
headline_print_headline: Five Aides to Party-Switching House Lawmaker Resign

abstract: U.S. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer proposed in a letter released on Sunday that at least four witnesses including acting White House Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney and former national security adviser John Bolton be subpoenaed to testify in the expected impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
snippet: U.S. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer proposed in a letter released on Sunday that at least four witnesses including acting White House Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney and former national security adviser John Bolton be subpoenaed to testify in...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer proposed in a letter released on Sunday that at least four witnesses including acting White House Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney and former national security adviser John Bolton be subpoenaed to testify in the expected impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Senate's Schumer Wants Mulvaney, Bolton, Others to Testify in Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: Senate's Schumer Wants Mulvaney, Bolton, Others to Testify in Impeachment Trial

abstract: Hyperpartisan politics and an implacable president may break Congress’s ability to check him.
snippet: Hyperpartisan politics and an implacable president may break Congress’s ability to check him.
lead_paragraph: When the process of impeachment drove President Richard Nixon from office in 1974, there was widespread celebration that “the system worked.” But the 1974 impeachment process may turn out to have been unique, a model for how it should work that has yet to be replicated — and perhaps never will be.

abstract: With the first Democratic nominating contests less than two months away, former Vice President Joe Biden is already looking beyond to Super Tuesday in March, when some of the biggest electoral prizes will be up for grabs.
snippet: With the first Democratic nominating contests less than two months away, former Vice President Joe Biden is already looking beyond to Super Tuesday in March, when some of the biggest electoral prizes will be up for grabs.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - With the first Democratic nominating contests less than two months away, former Vice President Joe Biden is already looking beyond to Super Tuesday in March, when some of the biggest electoral prizes will be up for grabs.

abstract: The senior U.S. Senate Democrat called on Sunday for the Republican-led chamber to demand testimony from four current and former White House aides in a trial expected early next year on whether to remove President Donald Trump from office.
snippet: The senior U.S. Senate Democrat called on Sunday for the Republican-led chamber to demand testimony from four current and former White House aides in a trial expected early next year on whether to remove President Donald Trump from office.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The senior U.S. Senate Democrat called on Sunday for the Republican-led chamber to demand testimony from four current and former White House aides in a trial expected early next year on whether to remove President Donald Trump from office.
headline_main: Schumer Seeks Testimony From Mulvaney, Bolton in Expected Senate Trial of Trump
headline_print_headline: Schumer Seeks Testimony From Mulvaney, Bolton in Expected Senate Trial of Trump

abstract: In the first nominating state, many Democrats feel a responsibility to identify a candidate who can win in states more diverse than their own.
snippet: In the first nominating state, many Democrats feel a responsibility to identify a candidate who can win in states more diverse than their own.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Iowa — They share awkward glances at events where nearly everyone looks like them. They take comfort in reminding one another that they propelled Barack Obama to the White House. They swear that their values and priorities are representative of more than a Corn Belt farm state.

abstract: A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
snippet: A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
headline_main: Democrat Lawmaker Opposed to Impeachment Will Switch Parties: Report
headline_print_headline: Democrat Lawmaker Opposed to Impeachment Will Switch Parties: Report
